                                <date>1958</date>. С. <biblScope unit="page">??–??</biblScope>.</bibl></sourceDesc></fileDesc><encodingDesc><tagsDecl>&amp;renditions;</tagsDecl></encodingDesc></teiHeader><text><body><entry xml:id="entry_arawyn_2" n="2" xml:lang="os"><form xml:lang="os-x-iron" type="lemma"><orth>arawyn</orth><form type="participle"><orth>aryd</orth></form></form><form xml:lang="os-x-digor" type="dialectal"><orth>arawun</orth><form type="participle"><orth>arud</orth></form></form><sense><tr xml:lang="ru"><q>оглашать сильным шумом</q></tr><note type="comment" xml:lang="ru"> (обычно, но не исключительно, про %sэхо%s)</note><note type="comment" xml:lang="en"> (usually, but not exclusively, about %secho%s)</note><tr xml:lang="en"><q>make a loud noise</q></tr><note type="comment" xml:lang="ru"> (обычно, но не исключительно, про %sэхо%s)</note><note type="comment" xml:lang="en"> (usually, but not exclusively, about %secho%s)</note></sense><exampleGrp><example><quote>toppy qæræj... bæstæ arydta</quote><tr xml:lang="ru"><q>ружейная пальба оглашала всю окрестность</q></tr><tr xml:lang="en"><q>rifle firing was heard throughout the neighborhood</q></tr><bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#src_Сека"/><biblScope>9</biblScope></bibl></example><example><quote>syvællætty cʼæxaxstæj kʼæʒæxtæ arydtoj</quote><tr xml:lang="ru"><q>плач детей оглашал скалы</q></tr><tr xml:lang="en"><q>the crying of children resounded through the rocks</q></tr><bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#src_Сека"/><biblScope>23</biblScope></bibl></example><example><quote>donæn jæ særsæræj arawy kom</quote><tr xml:lang="ru"><q>шум реки оглашает ущелье</q></tr><tr xml:lang="en"><q>the noise of the river resounds through the gorge</q></tr><bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#src_Xar._Zærdæ"/><biblScope>58</biblScope></bibl></example><example><quote>sæ zaræǵy qær kæmttæ arydta</quote><tr xml:lang="ru"><q>звуки их песен оглашали ущелья</q></tr><tr xml:lang="en"><q>the sound of their songs resounded through the gorges</q></tr><bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#src_F."/><biblScope>1957 I 9</biblScope></bibl></example><example xml:lang="os-x-digor"><usg><lang/></usg><quote>fæjjaw... ǧær nizzaruj; oj niffænzgæ i zæǧændor xwænxtæ, ǧædtæ niccarawuj</quote><tr xml:lang="ru"><q>пастух запевает громко; подражая ему, эхо оглашает горы, леса</q></tr><tr xml:lang="en"><q>the shepherd starts singing loudly; imitating him, the echo resounds through the mountains and forests</q></tr><bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#src_Iræf"/><biblScope>41</biblScope></bibl></example><example xml:lang="os-x-digor"><usg><lang/></usg><quote>arudæj bæstæ sæ toppaʒaǧdæj</quote><tr xml:lang="ru"><q>от их ружейной пальбы гремело эхо</q></tr><tr xml:lang="en"><q>their gunshots echoed</q></tr><bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#src_Bes."/><biblScope>109</biblScope></bibl></example></exampleGrp><exampleGrp><example><quote>toppy qæræj... bæstæ arydta</quote><tr xml:lang="ru"><q>ружейная пальба оглашала всю окрестность</q></tr><tr xml:lang="en"><q>rifle firing was heard throughout the neighborhood</q></tr><bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#src_Сека"/><biblScope>9</biblScope></bibl></example><example><quote>syvællætty cʼæxaxstæj kʼæʒæxtæ arydtoj</quote><tr xml:lang="ru"><q>плач детей оглашал скалы</q></tr><tr xml:lang="en"><q>the crying of children resounded through the rocks</q></tr><bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#src_Сека"/><biblScope>23</biblScope></bibl></example><example><quote>donæn jæ særsæræj arawy kom</quote><tr xml:lang="ru"><q>шум реки оглашает ущелье</q></tr><tr xml:lang="en"><q>the noise of the river resounds through the gorge</q></tr><bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#src_Xar._Zærdæ"/><biblScope>58</biblScope></bibl></example><example><quote>sæ zaræǵy qær kæmttæ arydta</quote><tr xml:lang="ru"><q>звуки их песен оглашали ущелья</q></tr><tr xml:lang="en"><q>the sound of their songs resounded through the gorges</q></tr><bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#src_F."/><biblScope>1957 I 9</biblScope></bibl></example><example xml:lang="os-x-digor"><usg><lang/></usg><quote>fæjjaw... ǧær nizzaruj; oj niffænzgæ i zæǧændor xwænxtæ, ǧædtæ niccarawuj</quote><tr xml:lang="ru"><q>пастух запевает громко; подражая ему, эхо оглашает горы, леса</q></tr><tr xml:lang="en"><q>the shepherd starts singing loudly; imitating him, the echo resounds through the mountains and forests</q></tr><bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#src_Iræf"/><biblScope>41</biblScope></bibl></example><example xml:lang="os-x-digor"><usg><lang/></usg><quote>arudæj bæstæ sæ toppaʒaǧdæj</quote><tr xml:lang="ru"><q>от их ружейной пальбы гремело эхо</q></tr><tr xml:lang="en"><q>their gunshots echoed</q></tr><bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#src_Bes."/><biblScope>109</biblScope></bibl></example></exampleGrp><etym xml:lang="ru">Старое сращение преверба %iа-%i с основой %irav-%i (%iru-%i) ‘шуметь’, ‘реветь’; ср. <mentioned xml:lang="sa"><lang/> <w>rav-</w> <gloss><q>реветь</q></gloss></mentioned><mentioned xml:lang="sa"><w/> <gloss><q>шуметь</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="sa"><w/> <gloss><q>греметь</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="sa"><w>rāuti, ravati, ruvati</w> <gloss><q>он ревет</q></gloss></mentioned>, , <mentioned xml:lang="ru"><lang/> <w>реветь</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="grc"><lang/> <w>ωρύομαι</w> <gloss><q>издавать крик</q></gloss></mentioned><mentioned xml:lang="grc"><w/> <gloss><q>реветь</q></gloss></mentioned>, , <mentioned xml:lang="la"><lang/> <w>rumor</w> <gloss><q>шум</q></gloss></mentioned><mentioned xml:lang="la"><w>ravus</w> <gloss><q>хриплый</q></gloss></mentioned>,  и пр.; на иранской почве, может быть, относятся сюда же <mentioned xml:lang="wbl"><lang/> <w>varüy- : varoid-</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="srh"><lang/> <w>varau-: varüd-</w> <gloss><q>выть</q></gloss></mentioned><mentioned xml:lang="srh"><w/> <gloss><q>лаять</q></gloss></mentioned>,  (<bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#ref_Shaw"/><biblScope>XLV 225</biblScope></bibl>).</etym><etym xml:lang="en">The old contraction of the preverb %iа-%i and the stem %irav-%i (%iru-%i) ‘make noises’, ‘roar’; cf. <mentioned xml:lang="sa"><lang/> <w>rav-</w> <gloss><q>roar</q></gloss></mentioned><mentioned xml:lang="sa"><w/> <gloss><q>make noises</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="sa"><w/> <gloss><q>rattle</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="sa"><w>rāuti, ravati, ruvati</w> <gloss><q>he is roaring</q></gloss></mentioned>, , <mentioned xml:lang="ru"><lang/> <w>реветь</w> <gloss><q>roar</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="grc"><lang/> <w>ωρύομαι</w> <gloss><q>let out a cry</q></gloss></mentioned><mentioned xml:lang="grc"><w/> <gloss><q>roar</q></gloss></mentioned>, , <mentioned xml:lang="la"><lang/> <w>rumor</w> <gloss><q>noise</q></gloss></mentioned><mentioned xml:lang="la"><w>ravus</w> <gloss><q>hoarse</q></gloss></mentioned>,  etc.; as for Iranian languages, maybe the following words are related to it as well: <mentioned xml:lang="wbl"><lang/> <w>varüy- : varoid-</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="srh"><lang/> <w>varau-: varüd-</w> <gloss><q>howl</q></gloss></mentioned><mentioned xml:lang="srh"><w/> <gloss><q>bark</q></gloss></mentioned>,  (<bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#ref_Shaw"/><biblScope>XLV 225</biblScope></bibl>).</etym></entry></body></text></TEI>